{#-
name: script-shebang-hygiene
summary: Script hygiene — never zsh shebangs; shebanged scripts need .sh/.py extension and chmod +x.
domain: engineering
audience: agent
severity: default
tags: [scripts, shebang, bash, hygiene]
scope: [any]
phase: [executing]
-#}
- Never use `#!/usr/bin/env zsh`. Use `#!/usr/bin/env bash` or `#!/usr/bin/env -S uv run --script`.
- Scripts with shebangs must have extensions (`.sh` or `.py`) and be executable (`chmod +x`).
